{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e26b9cab-d089-45a2-bb54-40f57fa12e29","content":"I can help point you in the right direction, though dump **analysis** is outside the scope of the tools I have available here (the `dump-collect` skill only covers **collecting** dumps, not analyzing them).\n\nHere are your main options for analyzing a `.dmp` file from a .NET app:\n\n### `dotnet-dump analyze` (cross-platform)\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\ndotnet-dump analyze <path-to-file.dmp>\n```\nUseful commands inside the session:\n| Command | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `clrstack` | Managed call stack of current thread |\n| `clrthreads` | List all managed threads |\n| `pe` (`printexception`) | Print the last exception |\n| `dumpheap -stat` | Heap overview |\n| `dso` (`dumpstackobjects`) | Objects on current stack |\n\n### LLDB + SOS (Linux)\n```bash\nlldb --core <file.dmp>\n(lldb) plugin load libsosplugin.so\n(lldb) clrstack\n```\n\n### WinDbg / Visual Studio (Windows)\nOpen the `.dmp` in **WinDbg** or **Visual Studio** → Debug → load with managed debugging.\n\n---\n\n**Quick triage recipe:**\n```\ndotnet-dump analyze my.dmp\n> clrthreads          # find the faulting thread\n> setthread <id>      # switch to it\n> clrstack            # see where it crashed\n> pe                  # print the exception\n```\n\nWould you like help with anything else, such as setting up dump **collection** for future crashes?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f18add51-879e-40da-9372-659ef5965b31","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file. Let me check the available skills - there's a \"dump-collect\" skill, but its description says it's for configuring and collecting crash dumps, and explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze, profiling or tracing.\"\n\nSo the dump-collect skill is not appropriate here. I should help the user directly with guidance on analyzing their dump file.","outputTokens":519,"requestId":"6808:237AB0:AEE9C2E:BE1BDCB:69FD42F7"},"id":"a769924e-b784-4116-816c-33464fd8c096","timestamp":"2026-05-08T01:57:25.125Z","parentId":"45a91022-58c7-47f5-8f3e-43bb2ace565f"}
